ctx.text: Lesotho’s montane grasslands support antelopes such as the grey rhebok, mountain reedbuck, common eland, and black wildebeest, alongside the iconic Burchell’s zebra. Small mammals like the woodland dormouse and Cape ground squirrel share the landscape with chacma baboons and carnivores such as the Cape gray mongoose, illustrating a high-country assemblage adapted to cool, open terrains.
